12 month contract, 7.5hr workday
Surry Hills, NSW - Hybrid/2 days WFH
JIRA, Confluence, Visio, Excel, PowerPoint, Word

Our client, a Commonwealth Government organisation whose focus is to provide support to Australian's living with disability, require the services of a Senior Business Analyst. 

Duties of the  Senior Business Analyst:

Develop a traceability framework for project team members to follow, to ensure all project deliverables link to an agreed business outcome via succinct and unambiguous business and technical requirements;
Elicit and document business and technical requirements to support the strategy and goals of the Agency as they relate to the Data & Analytics transformation program;
Analyse and document business process and data flows to provide current and future state context to support business and technical requirements;
Collaborate to ensure appropriate stakeholders are included in the development of business and technical requirements, including facilitating relevant workshops, meetings, working groups, etc.

Skills required

Demonstrated expertise documenting data and process flows to analyse and provide context to business and technical requirements;
Experience implementing Cloud Data Platform and/or Analytics applications and accompanying data architecture with specific focus on development of logical data models, and source to target mapping;
Strong proficiency with JIRA and Confluence, Visio, Excel, PowerPoint, Word;
Proficient data analysis skills (e.g. SQL, Python).

How to apply

To be considered for this role, please forward your resume to Coral by clicking the Quick Apply button. Please note that this role closes on Friday, 15 May 2026 @ midday. 

