ACT, NSW,QLD - Hybrid

Our client, a large Federal organisation is looking for the services of a Senior Business Analyst.

Duties of the Senior Business Analyst;

Lead end to end analysis & documentation of business, functional & non-functional requirements for Digital ID & Account products, across concurrent project & BAU changes;
Plan & facilitate requirements workshops, stakeholder interviews & walkthroughs with business SMEs, operations & technical teams to confirm scope, outcomes & constraints;
Translate technical inputs (architecture, APIs, integration patterns, security controls, environment constraints) into clear requirements artefacts that delivery teams can build & test against, including user stories, acceptance criteria & definitions of done;
Partner closely with technical resources (developers, architects, testers) to refine requirements, resolve ambiguity, identify solution options & validate feasibility, effort and dependencies;
Contribute to continuous improvement of analysis practices, templates & ways of working across the Digital ID and Account delivery team, aligned to agile delivery approaches.

Skills and Experience

Demonstrated experience performing business analysis on complex digital products or services, including requirements analysis & documentation across multiple stakeholder groups;
Strong capability in managing requirements traceability, dependencies & change impacts across parallel initiatives and BAU change, maintaining a coherent end to end view;
Demonstrated experience working in agile, multi-disciplinary delivery teams & supporting ceremonies such as refinement, planning & showcases;
Excellent written communication skills, with experience producing fit for purpose artefacts for both technical & non-technical audiences;
Strong analytical & problem-solving skills, including the ability to break down complex problems, define measurable outcomes & identify fit-for-purpose options to support informed decision making;
Experience using contemporary delivery & documentation tooling (for example Azure DevOps or equivalent for backlog management & traceability).


