McArthur is seeking an experienced EL1-equivalent Financial and Regulatory Business Analyst to support a Federal Government regulatory improvement program.

This is an initial 6-month contract/labour hire engagement, with potential extension options. The successful candidate will provide specialist analytical capability to support regulatory reform, cost modelling, resourcing analysis and benefit quantification.

This role would suit a strong EL1-level analyst with experience across financial analysis, regulatory reform, cost recovery, business analysis or government program improvement.

About the role

In this position, you will support a defined program of regulatory improvement work. Key responsibilities may include:

assessing the current cost model supporting a regulatory framework;
translating changes in regulatory settings into cost, resourcing and operational impacts;
supporting the development of alternative resourcing models;
quantifying benefits linked to regulatory changes;
identifying duplication, administrative burden and opportunities for process improvement;
preparing clear analysis, briefing material and recommendations for senior stakeholders; and
working collaboratively with policy, finance, regulatory and operational teams.

About you

To be successful, you will ideally bring:

experience at APS6/EL1 level or equivalent;
strong financial analysis, cost modelling or cost recovery experience;
experience supporting regulatory reform, business improvement or program review activities;
ability to translate complex regulatory or operational changes into practical financial impacts;
strong Excel, analytical and written communication skills;
sound judgement and the ability to work with limited direction;
experience preparing briefings, reports or recommendations for senior stakeholders; and
Commonwealth Government experience will be highly regarded.

Experience in regulated industries, agriculture, biosecurity, exports, compliance, cost recovery or regulatory burden reduction would be beneficial but is not essential.

Eligibility

Applicants must have minimum NV1 clearence. Australian citizenship and the ability to obtain or maintain relevant security checks may be required.

What's on offer

EL1-equivalent Federal Government contract opportunity
Initial 6-month engagement with extension options
Full-time hours, 37.5 hours per week
Competitive hourly rate plus superannuation
Opportunity to contribute to a high-profile regulatory improvement program

If you are an experienced financial, regulatory or business analyst looking for your next Federal Government contract, we encourage you to apply.
